# Commit Message Suggestions

- When work is complete or the user indicates they are about to commit/push, proactively suggest 1-3 commit message starters.
- Base suggestions on:
  - what is currently staged (preferred) or changed
  - recent commit message style in this repository
- Keep suggestions concise and immediately usable.
- Match project tone and naming style (e.g. path-prefixed style like `/login: ...` when appropriate).
- Prefer "why-focused" wording over purely mechanical "what changed" wording.
- If multiple logical messages are possible, provide a best pick plus 1-2 alternatives.
- Do not auto-commit; only suggest message text unless explicitly asked to commit.
